<span id="freeTextContainer2330061579363025388">I thought I would enjoy this book as it has two of my favorite things - time travel and Scotland. It just didn&apos;t work for me. The character of Shawn was so annoying. He had no redeeming qualities and it was not at all convincing that Amy would stay with him with the way he treated her. Niall&apos;s character was the exact opposite, all honor and selflessness. He was a Mr Perfect and the fact that they were so completely opposite just made the whole scenario even more unbelievable. I wasn&apos;t convinced </span>
  <span id="freeText2330061579363025388" style="display:none">I thought I would enjoy this book as it has two of my favorite things - time travel and Scotland. It just didn't work for me. The character of Shawn was so annoying. He had no redeeming qualities and it was not at all convincing that Amy would stay with him with the way he treated her. Niall's character was the exact opposite, all honor and selflessness. He was a Mr Perfect and the fact that they were so completely opposite just made the whole scenario even more unbelievable. I wasn't convinced that they would fit into the other one's time without people being more suspicious it wasn't them. The ending didn't work for me either. Very disappointing.</span>
